acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

bridgehubDepositBaseToken(uint256,bytes3.details: If the corresponding L2 transaction fails, refunds are issued to a refund recipient on L2.

params._amount: The total amount of tokens to be bridged.
params._chainId: The chain ID of the ZK chain to which deposit.
params._originalCaller: The `msg.sender` address from the external call that initiated current one.

constructor.details: Disable the initialization to prevent Parity hack.this contract is deployed in the L2GenesisUpgrade, and is meant as direct deployment without a proxy.

params._l1AssetRouter: The address of the L1 Bridge contract.

finalizeDeposit(address,address,address,.details: Finalizes the deposit and mint funds.

params._amount: The amount of the token transferred.
params._data: The metadata of the token transferred.
params._l1Sender: The address of token sender on L1.
params._l1Token: The address of the token transferred.
params._l2Receiver: The address of token receiver on L2.

params._assetId: The encoding of the asset on L2
params._transferData: The encoded data required for deposit (address _l1Sender, uint256 _amount, address _l2Receiver, bytes memory erc20Data, address originToken)

params._assetData: The encoded data, which is used by the asset handler to determine L2 recipient and amount. Might include extra information.
params._sender: The address of the deposit initiator.

returns._0: Returns calldata used on ZK chain.

params._data: The calldata for the second bridge deposit.
params._originalCaller: The `msg.sender` address from the external call that initiated current one.
params._value: The `msg.value` to be deposited on the target chain.

returns.interopCallStarter: InteropCallStarter corresponding to the second bridge call.

l1Bridge().details: The old name is kept for backward compatibility.

params._l2Token: The address of token on L2.

returns._0: The address of token on L1.

l2TokenAddress(address).details: However, the shared bridge can use custom asset handlers such that L2 addresses differ,or an L1 token may not have an L2 counterpart.

params._l1Token: The address of token on L1.

returns._0: Address of an L2 token counterpart

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

params.payload: Encoded function call data (must be finalizeDeposit)
params.sender: ERC-7930 Address of the message sender

returns._0: Function selector confirming successful execution per ERC-7786

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setAssetHandlerAddress(uint256,bytes32,a.details: Used to set the assetHandlerAddress for a given assetId.Will be used by ZK Gateway

setAssetHandlerAddressThisChain(bytes32,.details: The caller of this function is encoded within the `assetId`, therefore, it should be invoked by the asset deployment tracker contract.No access control on the caller, as msg.sender is encoded in the assetId.Typically, for most tokens, ADT is the native token vault. However, custom tokens may have their own specific asset deployment trackers.`setAssetHandlerAddressOnCounterpart` should be called on L1 to set asset handlers on L2 chains for a specific asset ID.

params._assetHandlerAddress: The address of the asset handler to be set for the provided asset.
params._assetRegistrationData: The asset data which may include the asset address and any additional required data or encodings.

params._assetId: The assetId of the legacy token.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

withdraw(address,address,uint256).details: A compatibility method to support legacy functionality for the SDK.

params._amount: The total amount of tokens to be withdrawn
params._l1Receiver: The account address that should receive funds on L1
params._l2Token: The L2 token address which is withdrawn

withdraw(bytes32,bytes).details: IMPORTANT: this method will be deprecated in one of the future releases, so contracts that rely on it must be upgradeable.

params._assetData: The data that is passed to the asset handler contract
params._assetId: The asset id of the withdrawn asset

withdrawLegacyBridge(address,address,uin.details: Finalizes the deposit and mint funds.

params._amount: The amount of the token transferred.
params._l1Receiver: The address of token receiver on L1.
params._l2Token: The address of token on L2.

bridgehubDepositBaseToken(uint256,bytes3.notice: Allows bridgehub to acquire mintValue for L1->L2 and L2->L2 transactions.

finalizeDeposit(uint256,bytes32,bytes).notice: Finalize the deposit and mint funds

getDepositCalldata(address,bytes32,bytes.notice: Generates a calldata for calling the deposit finalization on the L2 native token contract.

initiateBridging(uint256,address,uint256.notice: Function that returns an InteropCallStarter corresponding to the interop call. Effectively this initiates bridging,         BH part is processed within this function via `_bridgehubDeposit` call which also returns the data for an l2 call         on the destination chain (which will be processed with the returned InteropCallStarter from this function).

l1Bridge().notice: Returns the address of the L1 asset router.

l2TokenAddress(address).notice: Legacy function used for backward compatibility to return L2 wrapped tokenaddress corresponding to provided L1 token address and deployed through NTV.

pause().notice: Pauses all functions marked with the `whenNotPaused` modifier.

receiveMessage(bytes32,bytes,bytes).notice: Executes cross-chain interop messages following ERC-7786 standard

setAssetHandlerAddressThisChain(bytes32,.notice: Sets the asset handler address for a specified asset ID on the chain of the asset deployment tracker.

setLegacyTokenAssetHandler(bytes32).notice: Function that allows native token vault to register itself as the asset handler for a legacy asset.

unpause().notice: Unpauses the contract, allowing all functions marked with the `whenNotPaused` modifier to be called again.

withdraw(address,address,uint256).notice: Initiates a withdrawal by burning funds on the contract and sending the message to L1 where tokens would be unlocked

withdraw(bytes32,bytes).notice: Initiates a withdrawal by burning funds on the contract and sending the message to L1 where tokens would be unlocked
